The President visited South Delta Elementary School in Rolling Fork, Mississippi, where he expressed devastation at the destruction caused by a tornado. He stated that the federal government will stay as long as it takes to help with debris removal and provide support to the affected people. The President emphasized the importance of giving people hope, especially those who have lost loved ones. He acknowledged the incredible contrast between houses that are completely destroyed and those that remain standing. The President mentioned that he would provide further details about the situation shortly.